    "name": "committed_threshold_2016_narrow",
    "description": "Narrow sweep to pin the exact committed_split flip-point at 2016-block retarget. Companion to threshold_144_narrow (which pinned the econ_split boundary at ~0.29) and committed_2016_high_econ (which bracketed committed_split threshold in (0.20, 0.30)).\nRESEARCH QUESTION: committed_2016_high_econ and committed_2016_mid_econ confirmed the committed_split threshold is \u2208(0.20, 0.30) at 2016-block for both econ=0.55 and econ=0.78. Where exactly within that range does the flip-point fall? This narrow sweep tests committed=[0.22, 0.24, 0.26, 0.28] to bracket it precisely.\nPRIOR CONTEXT: - committed_split=0.20 \u2192 v26_dominant (all econ levels, all retarget regimes) - committed_split=0.30 \u2192 v27_dominant (all econ levels, all retarget regimes) - targeted_sweep1 (full 60-node, 144-block) found flip-point near committed\u22480.214 - Lite network may have a different flip-point due to different pool composition - This sweep characterizes the lite network threshold at 2016-block\nCOMMITTED_SPLIT INTERPRETATION (neutral=30%):\n  committed_split=0.22: v27=15.4%, v26=54.6%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.24: v27=16.8%, v26=53.2%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.26: v27=18.2%, v26=51.8%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.28: v27=19.6%, v26=50.4%, neutral=30%\n\nRun command (4 parallel namespaces):\n  kubectl create namespace cthr2016-0\n  kubectl create namespace cthr2016-1\n  kubectl create namespace cthr2016-2\n  kubectl create namespace cthr2016-3\n\n  python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input tools/sweep/committed_threshold_2016_narrow/build_manifest.json \\\n    --scenarios sweep_0000 --namespace cthr2016-0 \\\n    --results-dir committed_threshold_2016_narrow/results \\\n    --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 &\n  (repeat for sweep_0001/0002/0003)\n\nWall-clock: 4 scenarios \u00d7 13,000s parallel = 13,000s \u2248 3.6h\n",
